Product description

McKesson Perry Neoprene Sensitive Surgical Gloves

These McKesson Perry synthetic surgical gloves help protect both patients and caregivers during critical medical procedures and chemo treatments. The 100% synthetic neoprene glove delivers the performance of natural rubber latex without the risk of latex sensitization. It features an anti-slip, smooth finish with a continuous polymer coating for excellent dry- and damp-hand donnability. The sterile, powder-free gloves are chemo tested for the safety of healthcare staff.

At a Glance:

  • Continuous polymer coating makes it easy to take them off or put them on
  • Comes in cuff-length unisex sizes 5.5 to 9 with an average length of 12.2 inches
  • Sterilized with gamma radiation and without powder to reduce the chance of post-operative complications

Sterile Surgical Gloves


Keeps Hands Safe and Clean

Put the McKesson Neoprene surgical gloves on before performing medical, scientific, or other delicate work to create a barrier for the skin. They come sterilized with gamma radiation and have a cream color that helps identify glove breaks and minimize glare. The sterile gloves meet or exceed ASTM surgical glove standards.


Strong and Reliable Material

Rely on the Perry surgical gloves in several situations that require a strong yet flexible sterile latex material. They're powder-free, which helps stave off powder-related post-operative complications or reactions. Their smooth, anti-slip finish ensures the gloves don't catch or pull during procedures. The gloves come in unisex sizes 5.5 to 9 to fit different hand types and feature a hand-specific deisgn.


Comfortable Wear

Enjoy a comfy but snug fit thanks to the gloves' SureFit technology. The technology enhances roll-down protection to make sure gloves stay in place as you move. Their beaded cuff keeps the gloves strong and secure while stopping anything from dripping or getting inside. A continuous polymer coating makes the gloves wearable whether your hands are wet or dry. They come packaged in sterile right and left pairs to make it easy to get one glove for each hand.

About McKesson

For over 180 years, McKesson has supported providers with the medical supplies they need to care for patients and run a healthy business. McKesson offers more than 300,000 products from leading national brands as well as its own private product label, and a suite of services to help businesses and facilities provide quality care, improve business performance, and manage time and expenses. McKesson improves the business of healthcare to help everyone focus on what matters most: patient care.
